  "prompt": "What are the best fps games for PC for example: Battlefield?",
  "response": "There are many great first-person shooter (FPS) games available for PC, each offering its own unique gameplay experience. Here are some of the best FPS games, including Battlefield and others:\n\n1. **Battlefield Series**: Known for its large-scale battles, destructible environments, and vehicle warfare. Popular titles include **Battlefield 1**, **Battlefield V**, and **Battlefield 2042**.\n\n2. **Call of Duty Series**: A long-running franchise with various sub-series. Notable entries are **Call of Duty: Modern Warfare**, **Call of Duty: Warzone** (a free battle royale mode), and **Call of Duty: Black Ops Cold War**.\n\n3. **Counter-Strike: Global Offensive (CS:GO)**: A highly competitive multiplayer FPS that focuses on team-based gameplay and strategy. It has a robust professional scene and a strong community.\n\n4. **Doom (2016) and Doom Eternal**: Fast-paced, visceral shooters with an emphasis on fluid movement and intense combat. Doom delivers a single-player experience that is both challenging and satisfying.\n\n5. **Overwatch**: A team-based multiplayer FPS that emphasizes character abilities and teamwork. It features a diverse cast of heroes and various game modes.\n\n6. **Rainbow Six Siege**: A tactical shooter that focuses on teamwork and strategy. Players take on the roles of various operators, each with unique abilities, in hostage rescue or bomb defusal scenarios.\n\n7. **Halo: The Master Chief Collection**: This bundle includes several classic Halo games, bringing the iconic series to PC with enhanced graphics and online multiplayer.\n\n8. **Apex Legends**: A free-to-play battle royale game set in the Titanfall universe. It features unique characters and a fluid movement system.\n\n9. **Escape from Tarkov**: A hardcore survival shooter that combines FPS gameplay with RPG elements. Players scavenge for loot and compete in firefights in a realistic setting.\n\n10. **Metro Exodus**: A story-driven FPS set in a post-apocalyptic world. It combines elements of survival horror with immersive storytelling and exploration.\n\n11. **Far Cry Series**: While not purely FPS, these open-world games feature first-person shooting mechanics and are known for their expansive environments and engaging narratives.\n\n12. **Titanfall 2**: A critically acclaimed game that features both a single-player campaign and a unique multiplayer experience with parkour mechanics and giant mech battles.\n\nThese games represent a mix of competitive multiplayer, cooperative gameplay, and single-player experiences, so there's something for every type of FPS enthusiast.",
